SUMMARY:Slithering Truths
DESCRIPTION:We have superheroes among us. Snakes! \nIndia is home to at least 350 species\, and we’re discovering more every day. Their sense of smell unparalleled\, their heat-sensing abilities extraordinary. Born with superpowers\, snakes are supremely adaptable. Found across the Himalayas and the searing Thar desert\, in humid coastal belts\, fields\, towns\, and cities. Check your nearest flowerpot. \nPioneers of herpetological conservation\, Zai Whitaker and Rom Whitaker uncoil the secret lives of snakes in this eye-opening session. Expect the Big 4 venomous species\, surprising science\, and a fresh take on how we share our world with these remarkable neighbours. \nChildren\, bring your adults. Everyone is welcome \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/slithering-truths/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Books,Children's Books,Wildlife
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Thumbnail-4.jpg
END:VEVENT
